column3: Private fixed investment in new structures

column2: NA
1. Consists of office buildings, except those constructed at manufacturing sites and those constructed
by power utilities for their own use. Includes all financial buildings.
2. Includes buildings and structures used by the retail, wholesale and selected service industries.
Consists of auto dealerships, garages, service stations, drug stores, restaurants, mobile structures,
and other structures used for commercial purposes. Bus or truck garages are included in transportation.
3. Consists primarily of railroads.
4. Includes water supply, sewage and waste disposal, public safety, highway and street, and conservation
and development.
5. Consists of brokers' commissions on the sale of residential structures and adjoining land, title
insurance, state and local documentary stamp taxes, attorney fees, title abstract and escrow fees, and
fees for surveys and engineering services.
6. Excludes net purchases of used structures and brokers' commissions on the sale of structures.
7. Excludes net purchases of used structures and brokers' commissions and other ownership transfer costs.
